- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper deals with determining lower bounds on the border rank of bilinear maps, which is a problem in computational complexity. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents new methods for determining polynomials in the ideal of the variety of bilinear maps, which involves algorithmic techniques. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the concept of border rank, which is related to the rank of tensors and has connections to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper mentions the space of bilinear maps C^4 x C^4 -> C^4, which has applications in control theory. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with varieties of bilinear maps, which can be studied using techniques from algebraic geometry, a subfield of computational geometry.
